HEADWORD: Carangidae
<hw>Carangidae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>large family of
narrow-bodied marine food fishes allied to the mackerels, with widely
forked tails; chiefly of warm seas; it includes the
<stype>caranx</stype>, <stype>American bluefish</stype>, and the
<stype>pilot fish</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family Carangidae.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

